00:47:48.460 --> 00:47:53.100
I read the human interface guidelines,
you know, 10 years ago, 12 years ago.

00:47:53.140 --> 00:47:55.560
Well, you know what,
this stuff is really important.

00:47:55.560 --> 00:47:58.320
We're still thinking about
these things as we design Aqua.

00:47:58.380 --> 00:48:02.200
And you should be, as you design your
application for the platform,

00:48:02.230 --> 00:48:04.180
you should be thinking
about these principles.

00:48:04.210 --> 00:48:06.820
This stuff is not old.

00:48:06.850 --> 00:48:10.990
It's true, as true today as it
was when it was first,

00:48:11.090 --> 00:48:13.880
you know, thought up and presented.

00:48:13.890 --> 00:48:15.180
And I'll give an example.

00:48:15.310 --> 00:48:19.520
Feedback and communication,
I think one of the key characteristics

00:48:19.790 --> 00:48:24.660
of Aqua today is the fact that it uses
animation through sheets and drawers,

00:48:24.660 --> 00:48:26.940
the genie effect,
and different types of animations

00:48:27.080 --> 00:48:30.780
through expose and stuff to
communicate status to users.

00:48:30.810 --> 00:48:34.050
It takes us to a whole new level in
terms of communicating status and

00:48:34.050 --> 00:48:36.060
giving feedback as to what's going on.

00:48:37.080 --> 00:48:39.560
That's a real characteristic of Aqua.

00:48:40.120 --> 00:48:41.240
Modelessness.

00:48:41.240 --> 00:48:46.640
We've gone from being app modal for
many dialogues to being document modal.

00:48:46.640 --> 00:48:49.680
That's a trend towards modelessness.

00:48:49.680 --> 00:48:53.240
We're less modal now within the
application as a result of Sheets.

00:48:53.240 --> 00:48:56.560
So modelessness is a key
goal for us within Mac OS X.

00:48:56.560 --> 00:48:58.620
Aesthetic integrity.

00:48:58.720 --> 00:49:03.320
Aqua is just gorgeous compared
to what we had on Mac OS 9 or

00:49:03.410 --> 00:49:06.320
compared to anything else elsewhere,
I think.

00:49:06.990 --> 00:49:10.730
The aesthetic integrity, the gorgeous,
the beauty of Mac OS X, I think,

00:49:10.800 --> 00:49:12.920
just stands head and shoulders
above everything else.

00:49:12.960 --> 00:49:14.940
And if your app can't
fit into that world,

00:49:14.980 --> 00:49:17.140
it's going to stand
out like a sore thumb.

00:49:17.180 --> 00:49:19.450
And if you've been in my sessions before,
I've showed lots of

00:49:19.450 --> 00:49:20.840
