01:06:22.050 --> 01:06:25.040
Use standard controls.

01:06:25.040 --> 01:06:26.630
If you're delivering
software on the platform,

01:06:26.630 --> 01:06:28.280
it should look like
software on the platform.

01:06:28.280 --> 01:06:32.340
So there's a ton of stuff in the system,
whether it's AppKit or HIToolbox.

01:06:32.420 --> 01:06:36.260
And these are just some examples
of the different sizes of controls.

01:06:36.260 --> 01:06:37.860
Many controls were shipped last year.

01:06:37.860 --> 01:06:39.440
They're available in Panther today.

01:06:39.440 --> 01:06:41.740
They should be used not
in your main dialog boxes,

01:06:41.740 --> 01:06:44.070
but they should be used
in your utility windows.

01:06:44.070 --> 01:06:46.690
And don't mix and match control
sizes within the same window,

01:06:46.790 --> 01:06:49.380
whether it's a main window or
a dialog or utility window.

01:06:51.200 --> 01:06:52.220
All right, laying things out.

01:06:52.230 --> 01:06:55.800
These examples are dialog boxes,
but they could equally be main windows.

01:06:55.800 --> 01:06:59.980
And all of this is true for any window
type that you're designing on screen.

01:07:00.600 --> 01:07:02.770
So there's a tendency in
Aqua to center equalize,

01:07:02.780 --> 01:07:04.990
and I see people getting
this wrong over and over,

01:07:04.990 --> 01:07:07.850
so that's why I feel compelled
to talk about it for a moment.

01:07:08.750 --> 01:07:12.810
Center equalize doesn't mean that
everything gets center aligned,

01:07:12.920 --> 01:07:17.080
you know, so that you've got kind of
the centered effect on screen.

01:07:17.080 --> 01:07:18.320
This is a tab pane.

01:07:20.180 --> 01:07:23.630
So you basically lay out your content
according to the layout rules that

01:07:23.630 --> 01:07:27.330
are in the human interface guidelines
that I'm going to touch on shortly,

01:07:27.330 --> 01:07:27.330
but then you take

01:07:27.450 --> 01:07:30.190
I draw a bounding box around all
of it and then sort of center

01:07:30.210 --> 01:07:31.650
that box within the tab pane.

01:07:31.660 --> 01:07:33.560
And each tab pane might
have different edges,

01:07:33.560 --> 01:07:35.440
sizes, but it all gets centered in there.

01:07:35.460 --> 01:07:38.820
Here's another example
of where it's done.

01:07:38.820 --> 01:07:42.000
Notice if you drew,
notice the orange box around the content,

01:07:42.000 --> 01:07:45.820
that box is centered within the dialogue,
and then everything else

01:07:46.000 --> 01:07:48.200
is organized around that.

01:07:51.410 --> 01:07:53.240
Here is another thing
that needs to be done,

01:07:53.240 --> 01:07:55.300
and that is to right
align all of your labels.

01:07:55.300 --> 01:07:58.330
If you're labeling groups or labeling
radio buttons or what have you,

01:07:58.690 --> 01:08:01.290
those labels need to be right
aligned along their colons.

01:08:01.400 --> 01:08:03.240
They also need to have
colons behind them.

01:08:03.240 --> 01:08:09.280
Equally, you left align the
controls in those sets.

01:08:10.550 --> 01:08:12.160
And when you do that, it looks great,
actually.

01:08:12.160 --> 01:08:14.840
Oops, my apologies.

01:08:14.840 --> 01:08:17.820
The last one was basically
showing that within,

01:08:17.820 --> 01:08:20.920
under the size points there,
that that stuff is indented,

01:08:20.920 --> 01:08:23.800
but it's left aligned with sort of
the parent controls that it's under.

01:08:23.800 --> 01:08:26.720
This is all about providing
appropriate spacing.

01:08:26.720 --> 01:08:31.720
I still see stuff crammed onto
dialog boxes and no margins,

01:08:31.720 --> 01:08:34.010
and, you know, it just,
it doesn't feel like

01:08:34.010 --> 01:08:35.240
it's cleaned up nicely.

01:08:35.240 --> 01:08:38.060
And so there's appropriate
margins that need to be there.

01:08:38.430 --> 01:08:41.700
There's standardized
spacing for between items,

01:08:41.700 --> 01:08:44.660
between related items in
groups that are there.

01:08:47.300 --> 01:08:53.400
There's a larger spacing between
sort of less related groups.

01:08:55.360 --> 01:08:59.880
And then there's a larger spacing between
sort of distinct groups on screen.

01:09:00.180 --> 01:09:02.420
And you don't even
necessarily need the line,

01:09:02.430 --> 01:09:04.890
the horizontal line
that's on that screen.

01:09:06.160 --> 01:09:09.070
Action buttons go in the lower right,
nowhere else, lower right.

01:09:09.140 --> 01:09:13.040
And the OK button is on the right side,
and it's OK, O-K,

01:09:13.040 --> 01:09:18.920
not okie dokie or OKAY or
different variants of that,

01:09:18.970 --> 01:09:19.520
which I've seen.

01:09:19.520 --> 01:09:24.160
This is really something I see,
and if you get it right, it's great.

01:09:24.160 --> 01:09:26.180
It produces a really great design.

01:09:26.180 --> 01:09:30.300
But start your labels and check
boxes and radio buttons with

01:09:30.300 --> 01:09:34.770
verbs so that all the user really
needs to scan at a just glance,

01:09:34.770 --> 01:09:38.210
and they know that if dither is off,
it means it's not dithered, right?

01:09:38.220 --> 01:09:41.180
So it's really easy to figure
out what the check box or the

01:09:41.200 --> 01:09:43.210
radio button really represents.

01:09:43.650 --> 01:09:46.090
And there's a ton more
I could talk about,

01:09:46.090 --> 01:09:50.030
but I'm already down to like
five minutes left in the session.

01:09:50.030 --> 01:09:54.630
But things like quality icons and,
you know, quality rendered icons and

01:09:54.640 --> 01:09:58.960
well-organized toolbars,
you know, not populating your toolbars

01:09:58.960 --> 01:10:02.180
with hundreds of icons,
or even 30 or 15 is

01:10:02.180 --> 01:10:04.000
too many in many cases.

01:10:05.180 --> 01:10:06.370
You know, we can't get into that.

01:10:06.500 --> 01:10:08.340
File name extension support,
always display,

01:10:08.340 --> 01:10:10.320
use the display name for the document.

01:10:10.320 --> 01:10:12.130
If the user didn't name
it with an extension,

01:10:12.230 --> 01:10:15.930
they don't want to see the extension
in their document window title.

01:10:15.940 --> 01:10:19.550
Quality graphics, all of the graphics
that you draw on screen,

01:10:19.550 --> 01:10:23.660
whether it's static images or anything
else should be drawn with quartz,

01:10:23.810 --> 01:10:27.500
or at least if it's a static image
should be drawn by a graphic artist,

01:10:27.500 --> 01:10:28.960
a visual designer.

01:10:28.960 --> 01:10:31.380
And reserved keyboard shortcuts.

01:10:31.380 --> 01:10:35.560
Please honor the reserved keyboard
shortcuts that are... identified

01:10:35.630 --> 01:10:36.820
in the human interface guidelines.

01:10:37.400 --> 01:10:40.910
So, that's the fourth thing you can do,
the fourth area that you can focus

